President Donald J. Trump spoke with President Emmanuel Macron of France to discuss various topics. They talked about Trump's summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un and Trump reiterated the US goal of achieving complete denuclearization of North Korea. They also discussed finding a political solution to the situation in Syria through the United Nations Geneva process. Trump emphasized his goal of negotiating a comprehensive deal with Iran that addresses its nuclear and ballistic missile programs as well as its regional activities. Additionally, Trump called on the European Union to negotiate trade barriers reduction.